Place the chopped beef, gherkins, capers and shallot into a bowl and mix well.Add the mustard, Tabasco sauce, Worcestershire sauce, salt and freshly ground black pepper and mix well.To serve, spoon the steak tartare mixture onto a slice of plain or toasted dark rye or pumpernickel bread.Make a small dent in the top of the tartare and top with a fresh egg yolk. Eat immediately.